Give a brief history of the internet (1990-present)
The internet began in the 1960s as a military communications network, and was first made available to the public in the 1980s. The World Wide Web was developed in 1991, and the first web browser was released in 1993. The 1990s saw the rise of commercial internet access, and the development of new technologies such as HTML, JavaScript, and CSS. The 2000s saw the growth of social media, mobile devices, and the 'Internet of Things'. Today, the internet is a critical part of modern life, connecting billions of people around the world.

Describe to me some good coding practices 
Some good coding practices include: 

1. Using descriptive variable names to make the code more readable.
2. Separating concerns into different classes or functions.
3. Using comments to explain what the code is doing.
4. Testing code thoroughly before deployment.
5. Following standard coding conventions and guidelines.
6. Using version control systems to keep track of changes.
7. Writing clean and efficient code to avoid bugs.
8. Avoiding unnecessary complexity in the code.
9. Writing code that is scalable and adaptable to future changes.
10. Writing code that is easy to maintain and modify.
